On count 1, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.
On count 4, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 03-24-15 by 8:30 a.m.;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) pay court costs;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) submit to DNA sample and pay the surcharge on count 1 only;
6) defendant is only to consume prescribed drugs and in the prescribed doses;
7) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
9) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
10) Continue with any counseling currently engaged in or as recommended by the agent.
If revoked, the defendant has credit for 8 days.
$750.00 cash bail is to be applied to court costs.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
